                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Charleston</placeName>, <date>July\n                                                  11<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1852</date></p>\n                              <p>My dear Sir,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Your esteemed favor I recd some time ago<lb/> but\n                                        having nothing of importance to communicate I<lb/> delayed\n                                        until I recd Amt of your Bill against KKBE.<lb/> which had\n                                        been ordered for payment last month; —I shall<lb/> enclose\n                                        it with amt due for Binding &amp;c.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I saw <persName>Rev M Myer</persName> yesterday\n                                        and delivered your message<lb/> respecting the article in\n                                        the Phillippson paper. <persName>D<hi rend=\"sup\">r</hi>\n                                                  Myer</persName> requested<lb/> me to state that he\n                                        is <hi rend=\"underline\">not the author</hi> of the Article\n                                        in question<lb/> nor does he know who is, he intends to\n                                        write you on the<lb/> Subject. I <del>notice</del> observe\n                                        that you have noticed this attack<lb/> in the <add>?</add>\n                                        of the Occident. Can you my friend expect<lb/> that your\n                                        views should meet the approbation of the entire<lb/> public.\n                                        I wish you would adopt the high and dignified course of\n                                        allowing<lb/> the little dogs to bark—with out any regard to\n                                        their noise.<lb/> I pray you to keep such articles out of\n                                        your paper as <hi rend=\"underline\">this</hi><lb/> the <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">invitation for the</hi>\n                                        <sic>anonimous</sic> correspondent of Asmoneon to<lb/> come\n                                        forward with his name,—and your correspondents letter<lb/>\n                                        from <placeName>New York</placeName> about <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">your title of Revd</hi>\n                                        <del>to Mr who I</del><lb/> What do the public care for\n                                        these things, and it cannot<lb/> possibly add to your\n                                        reputation;—I take the liberty to say<lb/> so much to you\n                                        only for the purpose of bringing to your mind that<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> the man &amp; his principles must be of some\n                                        consequence if they<lb/> are publicly attacked, but that you\n                                        should notice all these attacks<lb/> is as preposterous as\n                                        it is <sic>unpracticable</sic>, in noticing them you<lb/>\n                                        make them of consequence. (whether they are so or not)—<lb/>\n                                        The sensitive plant: droops and yields to every breath of\n                                        air, while the Oak resists the tempest.<lb/> blast.—and, on\n                                        the morrow appear the fresher and more beautiful from the\n                                        Encounter</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3cf9js7m/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
